## Database Schema (Prisma — `backend/prisma/schema.prisma`)

> **Critical Prisma v7 note:** The `datasource db` block has NO `url` field (driver-adapter pattern). The MariaDB connection is passed programmatically via `PrismaMariaDb` adapter in `src/config/prisma.ts`. The `prisma.config.ts` files are only for CLI commands.

### Enums
```
Role: CITIZEN | NGO_ADMIN | VOLUNTEER | SUPER_ADMIN
RequestStatus: PENDING | UNDER_REVIEW | APPROVED | REJECTED | IN_PROGRESS | COMPLETED | CANCELLED
```

### Models (10 total)

| Model | PK | Key Fields | Relations |
|---|---|---|---|
| `User` | uuid | email (unique), passwordHash, role, firstName, lastName, phone?, isActive, createdAt | → requests[], ngoProfile?, volunteerProfile?, notifications[] |
| `NGO` | uuid | userId (unique FK→User CASCADE), name, registrationNo (unique), description?, address, city, state, isVerified (default false) | → requests[], resources[], volunteers[], joinRequests[], VolunteerInterests[], resourceAllocations[], VolunteerAssignments[] |
| `Volunteer` | uuid | userId (unique FK→User CASCADE), skills (JSON?), bio?, isAvailable (default true) | → ngoMemberships[], assignments[], joinRequests[], interests[] |
| `Request` | uuid | citizenId (FK→User), ngoId? (FK→NGO), title, description (Text), category, status (enum), urgencyLevel (Int, default 1), address/city/state, rejectionReason?, reviewedAt? | → assignments[], VolunteerInterests[], ResourceAllocations[] |
| `Resource` | uuid | ngoId (FK→NGO), name, type, quantity (Float), unit?, description? | → allocations[] |
| `VolunteerAssignment` | uuid | requestId + volunteerId (unique pair), ngoId, assignedBy (userId string), status (default "ASSIGNED"), notes? | Links Request ↔ Volunteer ↔ NGO |
| `NGOVolunteer` | uuid | ngoId + volunteerId (unique pair), joinedAt, isActive (default true) | Roster join table |
| `VolunteerJoinRequest` | uuid | volunteerId + ngoId (unique pair), message?, status (default "PENDING"), respondedAt? | Volunteer → NGO consent flow |
| `VolunteerInterest` | uuid | volunteerId + requestId (unique pair), ngoId, message?, status (default "PENDING"), respondedAt? | Volunteer → specific Request interest flow |
| `ResourceAllocation` | uuid | resourceId (FK→Resource RESTRICT), requestId (FK→Request CASCADE), ngoId, quantity (Float), notes?, allocatedBy | Tracks resource deductions per request |
| `Notification` | uuid | userId (FK→User CASCADE), type, title, body, isRead (default false) | Per-user in-app notifications |

