### Auth — `/api/v1/auth`
| Method | Path | Auth | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/v1/auth/register` | None | Create user; body below |
| POST | `/api/v1/auth/login` | None | Returns JWT; body below |
| GET | `/api/v1/auth/me` | Bearer JWT (any role) | Returns user profile (no passwordHash) |

**POST /register body:**
```json
{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "min6chars",
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "role": "CITIZEN",
  "phone": "+91...",
  "ngoProfile": { "name":"...", "registrationNo":"...", "description":"...", "address":"...", "city":"...", "state":"..." },
  "volunteerProfile": { "bio":"...", "skills":["Teaching"] }
}
```
- `role` optional, defaults to `CITIZEN`. Only `CITIZEN | NGO_ADMIN | VOLUNTEER` allowed on register (SUPER_ADMIN cannot self-register).
- `ngoProfile` required only if `role = NGO_ADMIN`.
- `volunteerProfile` optional even for VOLUNTEER role.
- Response `201`: `{ success: true, data: { user, token } }`

**POST /login body:** `{ "email": "...", "password": "..." }`
Response `200`: `{ success: true, data: { user, token } }`

